## 1 / 6 — Jump Squats
**40 seconds · Go hard**

- Feet shoulder-width, toes slightly out
- Squat to parallel — **thighs parallel to floor**
- Drive through heels, launch vertical
- Land soft, knees tracking toes
- No pause at the bottom — stay elastic

**Target:** 18–22 reps in 40s
**Common fault:** Heels lifting on descent — keep them **nailed to the floor**

> Breathe out on the jump. In on the way down.

