  / \   |    |   / \
        |    |
        |____|
         PLANK DOWN · UP
```

## 3 / 6 — Lateral Burpee
**40 seconds · Max effort**

- Stand beside an imaginary line (or a water bottle)
- Drop to plank, chest to floor, press up
- Jump both feet in, then **lateral jump** over the line
- Repeat facing opposite direction
- Arms stay active — don't let your lower back sag in the plank

**Target:** 8–12 full reps (each side = 1)
**Common fault:** Worming up from the floor — keep the body rigid on the press

> This is the money move. Don't half-rep it.

