@plane z=6 label="MOVE 5 · Hollow Body Rock"
```
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   )                (
  (    ← ROCK →     )
   )                (
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Arms overhead · legs 6" off floor
```

## 5 / 6 — Hollow Body Rock
**40 seconds · Core furnace**

- Lie on back, press lower back **flat** to floor
- Legs at 30° (harder) or 45° (scale), arms straight overhead
- Rock forward and back — use momentum, but **never lose the hollow**
- If lower back arches, raise legs higher or bend knees

**Target:** Continuous controlled rock for all 40s
**Common fault:** Disconnected rock — arms and legs should move as **one rigid unit**

> This is the exercise that separates gymnasts from everyone else.

