## 6 / 6 — Tuck Jumps
**40 seconds · Finish it**

- Feet hip-width, slight bend in knees
- Jump and **drive knees to chest** — grab them if you can
- Land soft on the balls of your feet, absorb with the whole leg
- Minimal ground contact — **plyometric rebound**
- Arms help: throw them up as you tuck

**Target:** 15–20 reps in 40s
**Common fault:** Jumping high but not tucking — the knees are what count

> Round complete. [[z=8|Check your round score.]]

